This paper discusses the automation of damage recovery in robots, which is a topic that falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to control the robot's behavior, which falls under the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of shape change as a method for function recovery also involves the use of sensors and actuators, which are components of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision to monitor the robot's behavior, which falls under the field of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning to optimize the robot's performance, which falls under the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
